<span id="freeTextContainer10005007083307779764">I’m blown away. Overwhelming sadness for the untold thousands of African-Americans persons brutalized in the aftermath of Reconstruction. Think slavery “ended” with the conclusion of the Civil War? Douglas Blackmon’s meticulously researched history will open your eyes if you have the fortitude to read it. More later when I’ve had a chance to let my emotions settle down. </span>

          </span>
